As per our [[VRCWiki:Conflicts of interest|Conflicts of interest]] policy, [[Community:Global Sign Language]] was removed as you are clearly credited as a primary contributor- and thus disallowed from creating a page on said content (or making any non-minor edits, such as spelling or grammatical errors). The community ''is'' notable enough to be included on the Wiki, but notability ''cannot'' be defined by anyone responsible for the community itself. It must come from the community's own interest and the available information ''about'' the world online.

If you'd like to see a page be created for the community, try reaching out to a maintainer or posting a request on our [https://discord.gg/ZNNds82Nht Discord server]! We ''admittedly'' don't quite yet have the most proper procedure for submitting page requests, but it's something we're working on making easier and more accessible to the public internet over time. I also VERY MUCH recommend publishing (or getting other involved parties to publish) any significant information about your community somewhere, so that third-parties can work with more substantial information for a better page (with proper citations too!)  [[User:Usr 578aa632-439b-4c41-9266-776323ba9ad2|Usr 578aa632-439b-4c41-9266-776323ba9ad2]] ([[User talk:Usr 578aa632-439b-4c41-9266-776323ba9ad2|talk]]) 01:09, 8 October 2024 (UTC)